      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh independence demonstrated with < 5% variation in RHI between medium and fine mesh.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted on baseline pump geometry at 5 L/min, 2500 RPM. RHI varied by 3.1% between medium (4.2M cells) and fine (9.8M cells) meshes. Medium mesh selected for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions replicated in simulation within documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rates and rotational speeds match published FDA benchmark experimental conditions. Fluid properties (viscosity, density) set to match phosphate-buffered saline used in physical experiments. Temperature held at 37°C consistent with in vitro protocol."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RHI within 15% of experimental hemolysis index measurements across all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted RHI compared against published in vitro hemolysis measurements for the FDA generic pump. Maximum deviation of 11.4% observed at the 6 L/min, 3000 RPM operating point. All 5 operating points within acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (RHI) directly corresponds to the clinical endpoint of interest and regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index is the primary regulatory metric for CPB pump hemolysis evaluation per FDA guidance. RHI < 1 relative to predicate device is the established acceptance criterion. CFD outputs directly mapped to this metric via the Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
